6 hours agoLast updated 6 hours ago Updated Monday to Friday only

Text forecast

Today

Tonight

Tonight, spells of rain and showers will gradually clear eastwards to leave a largely dry night with patchy cloud. However, the odd shower could linger in places. A gentle westerly breeze.

Tomorrow

Sunday

Tomorrow will see a mixture of patchy cloud and sunny spells to start. During the afternoon, a few sharp showers will develop; some of these may again be thundery. A gentle westerly breeze.

Outlook

Outlook for Monday to Wednesday

A band of patchy light rain may drift in from the north on Sunday, but otherwise, it will be a day of scattered showers and sunny interludes. Monday looks to continue similarly, with further scattered light showers and spells of sunshine. Tuesday will be yet another day of variable cloud amounts with a few showers in places.
